@startuml
title Viaverse Business Profile / Subscription — State Diagram

state "Business Profile" as BP {
  [*] --> BUSINESS_DRAFT
  BUSINESS_DRAFT --> PENDING_VERIFICATION : submit docs
  BUSINESS_DRAFT --> PUBLIC_ACTIVE : no review required
  PENDING_VERIFICATION --> PUBLIC_ACTIVE : approved
  PUBLIC_ACTIVE --> UNPUBLISHED : owner unpublishes
  UNPUBLISHED --> PUBLIC_ACTIVE : publish again
  PUBLIC_ACTIVE --> SUSPENDED : policy/admin
  SUSPENDED --> PUBLIC_ACTIVE : appeal/fix
  BUSINESS_DRAFT --> DELETED : delete
  PUBLIC_ACTIVE --> DELETED : account/business deletion
  DELETED --> [*]
}

state "Business Subscription" as BS {
  [*] --> SUBSCRIPTION_TRIALING
  SUBSCRIPTION_TRIALING --> SUBSCRIPTION_ACTIVE : payment method / trial converts
  SUBSCRIPTION_ACTIVE --> SUBSCRIPTION_PAST_DUE : payment failed
  SUBSCRIPTION_PAST_DUE --> SUBSCRIPTION_ACTIVE : paid
  SUBSCRIPTION_PAST_DUE --> SUBSCRIPTION_CANCELLED : grace period ended
  SUBSCRIPTION_ACTIVE --> SUBSCRIPTION_CANCELLED : owner cancels
  SUBSCRIPTION_CANCELLED --> [*]
}

note bottom
Profile state and subscription state are related but separate.
Subscription status may reduce premium visibility/tools,
but must not become pay-to-quote.
end note
@enduml
